parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank failure can cause fuel leaks, leading to fires, accidents, and stranded vehicles.
Fuel pump failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Turbocharger failure can cause loss of power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
VP44 pump failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Lift pump failure can cause engine failure, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Injector pump failure can cause loss of power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a sudden and violent shaking or wobbling
especially when driving over bumps or potholes; the steering wheel becomes difficult to control or freezes; the vehicle may drift or pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a sudden loss of steering control; the tie rod fractures or breaks; the vehicle may crash or drift to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The air bag fails to deploy or deploys incorrectly; the passenger side air bag may not deploy even when the driver side air bag does.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Injector and Lift Bump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injector and lift bump can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power or acceleration; the engine stalls or hesitates; a knocking noise is heard when the steering wheel is turned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and gearbox can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The output shaft fractures; the vehicle is unable to steer; the transmission fluid is lost; the engine is rough and stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and failure of the dashboard can cause distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents, and can also lead to electrical system failures, which can cause further safety issues.
symptoms: sharp edges and pieces of the dashboard can become loose and cause injury
the air conditioner may not work properly
low beam lights may flicker on and off.
